The article discusses Attorney General Jeff Sessions' claim that President Trump has delivered on his promise to reduce crime in the United States. Sessions highlights the importance of fighting crime, especially in communities that are already struggling. He mentions the efforts made by the Department of Justice in the past year, such as bringing cases against more violent criminals, prosecuting federal firearm offenses, convicting human traffickers and gang members, and arresting individuals involved in the opioid crisis. Sessions also mentions the decline in the number of officers killed in the line of duty and the support given to state, local, and tribal law enforcement partners. Overall, Sessions believes that the Trump administration's focus on law and order has made a positive impact on crime rates in the country.